{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4ca20ad7-1b2d-44c7-92e3-0c086d4985f3","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility layer by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk **4.0.0**, the SDK sets `EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner` to `true` and **no longer ships the VSTest adapter/runner**. This means `vstest.console.exe` (and `dotnet test` in VSTest mode) can't discover or run your tests.\n\n### Your options\n\n**Option A — Use the new Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner (recommended):**\n\nReplace `vstest.console` in your CI pipeline with a direct invocation:\n\n```sh\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- --treenode-filter \"/**\"\n# or simply:\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n```\n\n`dotnet test` in .NET 8+ automatically detects the new platform runner.\n\n**Option B — Re-enable VSTest compatibility:**\n\nAdd this property to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThis restores the VSTest adapter so `vstest.console` works again, but you lose the new platform's benefits (parallel execution, better diagnostics, etc.).\n\nWould you like me to apply either change to your project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"04b50d16-6980-458e-bde9-8019ffbe2917","outputTokens":318,"requestId":"BD06:2EBD81:1F200C6:2367479:6A07D623"},"id":"a7b09f92-594b-4939-9856-46bbfded13c1","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:27:55.879Z","parentId":"800e8ba5-af77-4cd2-bb5e-2a8469974717"}
